  "notes": "The LM7 is the most abundant junkyard LS engine in North America, found in millions of GMT800 trucks and SUVs. Iron block with aluminum heads, 9.5:1 compression. Uses truck intake manifold and 24x reluctor wheel (Gen III). Oil pan must be swapped for most car installations. Widely regarded as the best bang-for-buck LS swap starting point. High-mileage donors at 150k-250k miles routinely survive rebuilds or run as-is. Compatible with all Gen III/IV LS heads, intakes, and rotating assemblies with minor fitment checks.",
